


h3	spacestr

pre
	<text> = <b>spacestr</b> ( <number> )
	<text> = <b>spacestr</b> ( <number>, <pattern> )
p
	Return a text filled with <number> spaces.
p
	<tt>spacestr</tt> optionally accepts a fill pattern, which must be a text value. If this pattern is longer than 1 character, then the resulting text will be <number> * count(<pattern>) characters long. If the fill pattern is an empty text, then the result is an empty text too.
p
	e.g.:
pre
	var spc=spacestr(77);
	var foo=spacestr(123,""); put count(foo);
	put spacestr(100,"hello!");

